  "title": "Quality Control Technician (Jewellery/Manufacturing)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Conduct quality inspections on both incoming and outgoing products to ensure compliance with internal standards and specifications.</li>\n  <li>Carry out various product processes including quality checks, repairs, rework, and defect documentation.</li>\n  <li>Maintain accurate and complete records of QC results and supplier documentation in the system.</li>\n  <li>Assist in establishing SOPs and maintaining organized storage conditions and stock checklists.</li>\n  <li>Support general quality control operations and participate in improvement initiatives and ad-hoc assignments.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum NITEC in any discipline</li>\n  <li>At least 1 year of QC experience in <strong>Jewellery or Manufacturing industry.</strong></li>\n  <li>Familiarity with basic production workflows and strong attention to detail.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in MS Office; able to work independently and learn quickly.</li>\n  <li>Good communication and coordination skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in <strong>MS Word</strong> to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R1326740</p>",
